#4633
Wildflower Glade~
Sunlight pours into this broad glade where @@Gwildflowers crowd every open patch of soil@@N. Bumblebees move steadily between blossoms, carrying pollen on their legs. The scent of meadowsweet and yarrow drifts thickly through the warm air. Butterflies drift lazily through the brightest patches near the center of the glade.
