Protected Wetland Edge~
Boardwalk planks mark the preserve boundary at the edge of a protected wetland basin. @@GThe wood is damp and slightly springy underfoot where moisture seeps from the marsh.@@N Preserve signs ask visitors to stay on the boardwalk to protect nesting habitat from trampling.
