Rootbridge Descent~
Woven roots from the oldest trees descend from the sacred grove into a network of older preserve passages below. @@GThe roots form natural bridges and handholds along the steep and winding descent.@@N Light from above filters through the dense canopy in shifting @@Ggreen@@N shafts, giving the passage an eerie calm. The walls of the descent are earth and root, cool and damp to the touch. The warden keeps a second station here at the base of the descent, where the old preserve tunnels begin.
